        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 4:05PM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 404 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Anchor Dam, which is 26 miles south of Meeteetse,
moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of west central Hot
Springs County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
